			<div class="content" id="post-content-2260192">
									

<p>This storyline is open for business.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Credits.</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Credit to Clef for outright rewriting a whole lot of this to make it better. Credit to Kaktus for writing the Reading tab.<br />
Credit to Wogglebug for initial work on format. Credit to Mann, Light, Troy, Bright, Crayne, Photo, Decibelle, Zyn, Blaroth, Riemann, Dexanote, Eskobar, Roget, Silber, Ireul, and a whole bunch of other people for looking this over and giving extensive feedback. (Let me know if I forgot to credit you explicitly.)</p>
</div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Hide</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Anyone can contribute to this storyline if they wish. Feel free to tag your Tales or SCPs with &quot;resurrection&quot;.</p>
<p>If you have a draft or a posted story that you want posted on this hub, just propose it in the comments here.</p>
<p>IDEAS&#8230;</p>
<ul>
<li>How do your SCPs and characters fit into Resurrection?</li>
<li>Rumors about Alpha-9 are spreading fast. What do some of the humanoid SCPs think about this?</li>
<li>Alpha-9 hasn't been officially approved yet. Some O5s support it, some O5s oppose it. What do the staff of the SCP Foundation think of it?</li>
<li>Site-19 was destroyed years ago by Kondraki. Some portions of it are still cordoned off, semi-permanently. Are there anomalies still in there, which have gone unnoticed for almost a decade?</li>
</ul>
<p>This post will be edited as the storyline expands and updates.</p>

