			<div class="content" id="post-content-2260713">
									

<blockquote>
<p>To me it seems more like they are re-opening possible paths for our creativity that, in the past, had been closed because of taboo.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I'm repeating myself here, as I've spoken to this in my above reply to Clef. But I cannot emphasize enough how much I disagree with this point. The idea that pieces written in the traditional SSAA style are &quot;taboo&quot; is completely absurd. Certain users will usually criticize the use of these characters and settings when they appear (and I'll note that I have actually supported pieces featuring these elements in the past), but this notion that these kinds of articles are somehow deleted on sight is completely false. And that makes it a weak premise from which to base concerted action.</p>

							</div>

								
					
