				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mistbourne" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1665706); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1665706&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610161927" alt="Mistbourne" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1665706)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/mistbourne" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1665706); return false;" >Mistbourne</a></span> <span class="odate time_1427718775 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">30 Mar 2015 12:32</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2260293">
									

<p>When I first came to the site, it was smack-dab in the middle of the &quot;golden age&quot; DrClef alludes to above. I read a lot as a lurker, and enjoyed the cross-links, the avatars, and the bits of silly mixed in with the darkness.</p>
<p>I got busy with life, and lost track of the site for a while. I came back after Fish pulled his disappearing act, much to my confusion, and saw the radical change in site culture that resulted. We lost something there, and while it didn't kill the site for me, it wounded it severely.</p>
<p>Words cannot describe how happy I am to see some of the more immersive elements, what others would call &quot;silly&quot; or &quot;lolFoundation&quot;, come back, even in a limited form.</p>
<p>Who knows? Maybe this'll finally give me the push I need to stop lurking and start writing for the site.</p>

							</div>

								
					
